cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on object instance detection in cluttered indoor environments, which is a core functionality for service robots. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a method to generate synthetic datasets with minimum human effort, which involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks, and addresses the domain gap problem, which are topics that fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
